parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The persistent brake squeal or noise can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Abnormal squeaking sound from the rear of the vehicle
brake squeal at low speeds (usually under 10 MPH)
constant squeaking or loud noise when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of braking power can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
The tailgate opening and closing randomly while driving can cause loss of cargo, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The tailgate opens and closes randomly
opens when locking or unlocking the vehicle
opens when opening the driver-side door

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning trailer brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The "Service Trailer Brake System" warning message appears and beeps continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear camera can reduce visibility, increase the risk of accidents, and make it difficult to park or maneuver the vehicle.
The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: and the auto-start feature does not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden downshifting of the transmission can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, especially when towing a trailer.
symptoms: The vehicle downshifts from 8th to 7th or 6th gear
and potential fishtailing of the trailer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling line can cause the transmission fluid to leak, leading to transmission failure and stranding the driver.
symptoms: Transmission fluid sprays out of the motor
and the transmission cooling line comes apart at the crimp connection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The moisture intrusion into the transfer case can cause corrosion to the sensor, leading to grinding noises, "Service 4WD" light illumination, and potential loss of control.
symptoms: grinding noise/sound within the front axle transfer case

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of carbon monoxide into the vehicle cabin can cause poisoning, leading to serious health issues and potential loss of consciousness.
symptoms: loss of feeling in the body

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DEF tank heater can cause the vehicle to go into limp mode, leading to reduced performance and potential safety risks.
